---
title: Cheesy Beef Enchiladas with tomato and scallion salsa
description: The name of this popular Mexican dish derives from two Aztec words meaning 'chilli' and 'flute'—references to its rolled-up nature and the sauce it's often eaten with. These particular enchiladas are stuffed full of spiced beef and cheese and paired with a zingy salsa.
