Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack}.

Halve the @lemon{1}. Cut half into thick wedges and juice the rest.

Chop the @tomatoes{2} into small pieces.

Trim and grate the @carrot{1}(trimmed and grated) (no need to peel). Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

In a #bowl{} mix the tomato with half the scallion then season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and 1 tsp lemon juice (double for 4p).

Heat a #pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once the pan is hot, add the @Irish beef mince{250%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Season with salt and pepper.

Once mince is cooked, add half the grated carrot, kidney beans, @ground cumin{1%sachet} and @ketchup{1%sachet} to the pan.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} and mix together.

Cook for ~{1%minute} and remove from the heat.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and @sugar{to taste}.

Lay the @tortilla{8} on a #board{}, spoon some of the mince down the centre of each, then roll them up to enclose the filling.

Drizzle a little @oil{to taste} into the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{} then lay in the wraps.

Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge underneath so they don't unroll.

Top with the @grated cheese{50%g}.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @avocado{1} and scoop out the flesh.

Use a #fork{} to mash it. Add a squeeze of lemon juice.

Season to taste salt and pepper then mix well to combine.

Once cooked, remove the enchiladas from the oven.

Divide between #plates{}.

Top with the smashed avocado.

Serve with tomato salsa and remaining carrot and lemon wedges.

Garnish with remaining scallions.